title: get IP(v4) addresses for running instance(s)
pid: 485410f8-47f8-49d1-91fc-51fa9aafcb8b
body: |2-
  First [[id:ce3a8d0b-7e44-4457-a7d6-23c33288f75c][describe them all in a file]].
  Then grep the file:
    grep "\"PublicIp\"" all-running-instances.json
  or write *that* to a file:
    grep "\"PublicIp\"" all-running-instances.json \
      | grep -o "[0-9].*[0-9]"                     \
      | uniq                                       \
      > ip-addresses.txt
